Cholesterol in HDL [Mass/volume] in Serum or Plasma

tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased HDL cholesterol (34.8 mg/dL). Glycemic, renal, electrolyte, and lipid profiles are otherwise unremarkable. Low HDL is a cardiovascular risk factor; lifestyle modification and cardiovascular risk assessment are recommended. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
